===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
The reduced form of the character {{och-l|鬻}}, which was an ideogrammic compound and the original character for "congee".

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=鬻}}

Related to {{och-l|育}}, {{och-l|鬻|to nourish}} ({{zh-ref|Karlgren, 1956}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}). {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (1998)}} originally derive {{och-l|粥|tr=*t-ljuk}} from {{och-l|育|tr=*ljuk}}, but later, {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}} derive {{och-l|粥|tr=*t-quk}} from a root {{m|und|*quk||to nourish}}, which is related to {{och-l|育|tr=*m-quk}}, as well as {{och-l|畜|to nourish|tr=*qʰuk}}.

Alternatively, it may be related to {{cog|bo|ཐུག་པ||Tibetan-style soup, broth, gruel, porridge}} ({{zh-ref|Bodman, 1980}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

